---

## Installation

Clone the repository

```
git clone <repository-url>
cd product-api
```

Install dependencies

```
npm install
```

---

## MongoDB Setup

Start MongoDB

```
mongod --port 27017 --dbpath C:\data\PORT_27017
```

Example connection string

```
mongodb://localhost:27017/productDB
```

---

## Redis Setup

Start Redis server

```
redis-server
```

Check Redis connection

```
redis-cli
ping
```

Expected response

```
PONG
```

---

## Run the Application

Start server

```
node server.js
```

Server runs on

```
http://localhost:5000
```

---

## Run using PM2 (Production Mode)

Install PM2

```
npm install pm2 -g
```

Start application

```
pm2 start ecosystem.config.js
```

Check running processes

```
pm2 list
```

View logs

```
pm2 logs
```

---

## API Endpoint

### Get Product by ID

```
GET /api/product/:id
```

Example

```
http://localhost:5000/api/product/69b66f87fc1141fc0762a081
```

---

## Redis Caching Flow

1. API request received
2. Redis cache checked
3. If cache exists → return cached response
4. If cache miss → fetch from MongoDB
5. Save result in Redis with expiration
6. Return response

Cache TTL: 60 seconds

---

## MongoDB Indexing

Indexes improve query performance.

Example

```
productSchema.index({ Supc: 1 });
```

Check indexes

```
db.products.getIndexes()
```

---

## Useful PM2 Commands

Restart application

```
pm2 restart product-api
```

Stop application

```
pm2 stop product-api
```

Delete process

```
pm2 delete product-api
```

Monitor CPU and memory

```
pm2 monit
```

